# Create Todos Command

When the user says "add a todo", "create a todo", "add to todo", or similar:

## 1. In-code todo (Todo Highlight)

Use for tasks that belong to a specific file or feature:

- Add: `// TODO: description` (or `// FIXME:` for bugs, `// NOTE:`, `// HACK:`, etc.)
- Place at the relevant location (top of file, above function, or exact line)
- Todo Highlight picks up: TODO:, FIXME:, NOTE:, IDEA:, REVIEW:, DEBUG:, OPTIMIZE:, etc.

## 2. Project todo (Todo+)

Use for general tasks, backlog items, or when the user doesn't specify a file:

- **File**: `features.todo` in project root (Todo+ / Todo extension: set `todo.file.name` to `features.todo` or include `**/features.todo`)
- **Format** (TaskPaper-style, 2-space indent):
  ```
  ProjectName:
    ☐ Task description
  ```
- Symbols: ☐ (box), ✔ (done), ✘ (cancelled). Optional tags: `@est(1h)`, `@high`, etc.
- Add new items under the relevant project (or "Todo:" if none). Indent with 2 spaces.
- Default content for new file: `\nTodo:\n  ☐ Item\n`

## When to use which

- **In-code**: "add a todo here", "todo for this function", task belongs to one file
- **Project**: "add a todo", "create a todo", "add to backlog", general task
